=== Validation rules (each must hold for every extracted item) ===

1. The cited `session_id` must be **strictly after** s{{ outdated_session_introduced }}
   (so s{{ active_session_introduced }} or later is fine; the
   outdated session itself is not eligible).
2. `evidence_text` must appear **verbatim** somewhere in the cited
   session — copy a contiguous span of text from a single user or
   assistant turn. Do not paraphrase. Do not splice from multiple
   turns.
3. The evidence must support the SAME target slot as v2 (don't
   extract evidence about an unrelated topic).
4. The evidence must support the SAME candidate active state (must
   not contradict v2 or point at a different active value).
5. The evidence type must match the declared `implicit_drift_type`
   (per the definitions above).
6. The evidence must NOT use any explicit replacement language. The
   following phrasings disqualify an evidence item:
     - "I switched from X to Y"
     - "no longer use X" / "no longer X"
     - "from now on"
     - "going forward"
     - "I changed my mind"
     - "replace X with Y"
     - "the old X" (referring to v1 by name)
     - "now I just/only X"
     - "I VERB now" (e.g. "I run now", "I write now")
     - "cutting X out entirely"
     - "stick to X only"
     - "new rule" / "new policy" / "new routine"
   Skip any candidate evidence span that contains these phrases.
7. The evidence must be a **personal, behavioral, or
   preference-grounded** statement by the user (or assistant
   confirming such a statement) — not a one-off mention of the
   active value's name in passing.

=== Required output format ===

Output ONLY a JSON object with this exact shape. No prose outside the
JSON. No markdown code fence.

{
  "active_evidence": [
    {
      "session_id": "s<N>",
      "evidence_text": "<verbatim span from session N>",
      "why_it_supports_active_state": "<one sentence rationale>"
    },
    ...
  ]
}

Produce **2–3 items**. Prefer 3 if 3 distinct, independent spans
exist. If you cannot find 2 items satisfying every rule, output
exactly:

{"active_evidence": []}

The downstream validator will reject any extraction with fewer than
2 items, so an empty list is a deliberate "I cannot extract valid
evidence" signal — better than fabricating.
